				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{\Delta }}G\left( t \right) = \left( { - \frac{1}{K}} \right)\left( {\frac{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}P\left( t \right)}}{P}} \right)$$\end{document}where K is a calibration factor experimentally determined from the dielectric properties of the QD films and the resonance characteristics of the microwave cavity. The end-of-pulse (peak) photoconductance, ΔGpeak, is related to the yield mobility product (φΣμ) using the equation:2ΔGpeak=βqeNμe+μh=βqeI0FAφΣμ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
